< Review>
I've been here a couple of times in the last month or so and wasn't disappointed either time. They have a HUGE menu with a ton of offerings which sometimes makes it hard to decide what to order. What a great problem to have!
The staff is extremely friendly and is truly the highlight of this establishment.
Super laid back diner with an at home feel.

For reference I've had the rib-eye and eggs (delicious) as well as the pastrami Swiss burger. Both times I've had the chili-cheese fries and both times they left a little flavor to be desired.
Overall a solid establishment that I will be frequenting in the future.</Review>

Good food, but slow, slow, slow.  It was my first visit and I intend to go back because everyone can have a bad day.  Ill update when I do.

I'm updating!  Finally went back and slow is definitely the norm here.    The place is small and clearly loved as it's usually busy.  The food is good too.  The problem is the wait time from order to delivery.  Its breakfast and we waited easily over 30 minutes for simple breakfast - eggs, pancakes, etc both visits.     If you've got the time and patience, I recommend.  If you don't, try somewhere else.<//text>

< Review>
I visited West Coast Dental for the first time because I had a major tooth ache. When I first walked in I didn't know what to expect, especially since
my fear of the dentist has made me put off dealing with my tooth ache too long. However, the pleasant service I received when I checked-in calmed my anxiety. <Date>1537246790785</Date><Rating>5<//Rating>< Review>
I've never been to a true cycle class before until some of my friends convinced me to try it out on class pass. I then was hooked from the amazing experience I had from my first class at cycle bar Hillcrest! I love that they provide you all the essentials you need to make your ride enjoyable and hassle free. They provide you with the clip in shoes, no rental necessary, free lockers, towels, and the bonus added treat at the end of class are the eucalyptus infused towels during cool-down! If you've never cycled before, they go over how to set up your bike, the instructor goes over what the positions are at the beginning of every class no matter if you're experienced of a first time rider, and help you clip in over and over again if you're still not use to getting the shoes into the pedal. I love coming here, and the location is great! Everything is in this town center. Parking is pretty easy, especially during the morning classes, very accessible! The instructors are nice, great motivators, and so very helpful. They also always have good package deals. Try out cyclebar yourself and you're sure to come back for another class!</Review>

<Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
I absolutely love CycleBar! From the moment you start up the stairs you smell their signature scent that immediately lets you know you are in for a treat!

< Review>
First off, this hospital is great. The service, the speed, the attentiveness, staff, and food (especially the food). Not only are almost all the staff that I encountered professional; but they're also very personable and many of them went above and beyond to spend extra time with me -- talking to me and making conversation to help the time pass quicker while I was there.

The issue that a lot of people on here aren't taking into account is that they're not comparing this hospital to other ones.  When compared with other hospitals in california (and I've been a patient at a good number of them throughout my life for chronic issues), this hospital's definitely one of the better ones. And this includes ER wait times, food, and service from the staff.</Review>

I thought a hole was being burned through my stomach...So needless to say I had to come back.  I had just gone through major reconstructive surgery on my face.  The nurses and people out front in the emergency room made me feel like I was a joke even though I had not slept for days and just just come out of major reconstructive surgery.  I had been up for 48 hours on no sleep.  I was compacted with constipation due the meds I had been taking before and after the surgery.  My gastritis was extremely flared up.  I was swallowing big blood clots due to facial surgery... They didn't even give me a bed nor a blanket.  Then from the lack of sleep and not feeling well and being left alone for so long I started to panic... I asked to talk to someone in behavioral health, they acted like they had someone on sight and then just left me alone for hours again.. I was in so much pain and panicking ... NO ONE SEEMED TO CARE NOR BE compassionate!    They finally got me on the phone with a crisis line.  But not once did they make me feel comfortable at Feather River Hospital.  I had a dirty bed and was freezing and thirsty..  I wonder why the hell a hospital could be so under staffed and non compassionate! There is so much more I could say, but I am just going to say it was the worst experience I have ever had at a hospital in my life! This started a chain panic attack that lasted for hours after seeing feather River.  I felt so sick, lost and hopeless!  I finally went to Enloe in Chico where they seemed like angles and they helped me through all my systems.  They didn't let me leave until I was better! They cared at Enloe! Thank you so much Enloe!   I am NEVER going back to Feather River Hospital EVER!<//review>

< name>
Quinn Griffith<//name>
<Pictures>None<//Pictures>< review>
I would rate this place 0 stars if I could. I tried to type my whole horror story here, but apparently Google has a word limit. This place has the worst communication, and lacks all basic notions of human decency. They no compassion, understanding or empathy skills. They will have you go in for appointments just to waste your time and bill your insurance provider for it. If you ever had the misfortune of coming here, its probably because you're on Denti-Cal. They love to take advantage of being a Denti-Cal provider. If you're on Denti-Cal, they will view you as a money bag. They took x-rays even when they weren't needed, as I had some I could've sent them from my last dentist. They had me show up for surgery one day just to tell me that my tooth was too close to the nerve, so they needed to file for sedation approval with Denti-Cal. Appointment fee they just exploited from Denti-Cal right there.This is a conclusion even Patrick Star could've come to just by looking at the x-ray. When I finally did go for my wisdom teeth removal surgery 5 months later after first seeing them, it was one of the worst days of my life. they gave me two days notice to find. a driver who could stay on the premises during my surgery, and when I wet in and tried to explain to them I could make that happen, the receptionist says no you need a driver or this isn't happening today. I tell her we are in a effing pandemic and you guys only gave me two days notice to find a driver who could STAY. Her attitude falls to the floor, and then has the audacity to say "It's always something with you every time you come here, isn't it?" I respond by saying well maybe it's because your customer service as a business is sub-prime and there's always a reason to complain about something at this god-foresaken place. She hands me forms to sign, and says that they won't do it unless the driver stays. My driver says its fine, he can stay in his car and use his wifi hotspot, since the clinic refused to offer him wifi to do his work with. We then are directed to sit in the car and wait till called to come in. We sit in the car for AN HOUR. There was no reason for them to schedule me at 8 in the morning for 5 minutes of paperwork when they actually didn't open till NINE. So stupid. Then when I finally go in for surgery, they take my phone and don't tell me why, then they put me on what I guessed was an IV, but apparently was the sedative. Or maybe it was the thing they attached to my nostrils. Either way, they didn't announce to me they were going to put me under nor checked to make sure I was mentally ready. After I woke up, apparently I was crying and screaming. This was when the staff showed their true colors. Instead of trying to calm me down and show some basic human decency like compassion and understanding, they said "stop crying you're scaring the other patients." These people don't see you as human. All Western Dental sees its customers as is a money bag. They lack any basic customer service skills. When I couldn't stop crying, they forced me into a wheelchair and shoved me into my roommates car. I will never go back to this place. Don't waste your time, your money, or your mental sanity on this place. Ever.</review>

< Text>
DO NOT GET BRACES HERE!!!!
I went to western dental to get braces after wanting them for years, I had an overbite and crowding on my bottom teeth. I‚Äôve consulted with other orthodontists and they have told me my case would at minimum take two years to correct. After a year with western dental my teeth were very clearly not done and the ortho (who constantly changed because they cannot keep one permanent which begs to question how they are capable of studying all these cases to do treatment when they have these random orthos cycling in and out every few weeks) told me to double up on rubber bands, my new ortho told me that would have caused gum damage and god knows what else and this was where I really began questioning things.

Soon after they began to tell me my ‚Äúcontract was ending.‚Äù There was no contract, I was paying for the whole treatment out of pocket and it was stated the amount I was paying would cover everything but suddenly a contract somehow was ending. This meant they expected me to PAY MORE to keep my braces with them, I was beyond confused and they began telling me I‚Äôve used all my slot for the year (12 months once a month) yet I had not come in every month of the year due to their constant rescheduling. I asked to see when they had scheduled me on their computers and they had in fact made false records of me coming in.

I have had appointments scheduled with a month prior but when I‚Äôd show up they‚Äôd occasionally be so busy that I would have had to wait for 2 or more hours to even be seen and I wasn‚Äôt allowed to leave or I wouldn‚Äôt be seen. The people in the back rooms will leave you sitting sometimes up to an entire hour or more while they gossip and sit around. The place is incredibly unprofessional, untrustworthy and honestly I‚Äôm worried for anyone who has any work done here because they clearly do not care for your well-being, only money. I know people who also have had horrible experiences here and I honestly cannot believe I ever trusted them with something so important to me.

I wasted a year here paying out of pocket. These people will leech off you if it isn‚Äôt covered by insurance and will attempt to lie to you to see what else they can get from you.

Please do your research about this place, you‚Äôll be surprised by what else you find.< /Text>

Megan Jensen</user_name>
<date>1555467216785<//date><Rating>1< /Rating><review>I‚Äôm not sure how all of these positive Google reviews got here, nor how they stopped me from going to Yelp to get true reviews of this place, but please do your due diligence and go to Yelp. You can believe the many negative reviews here before going to Western Dental on Olive Avenue.

It would have saved me 2.5 hours of being poorly treated while patiently waiting for a teeth cleaning from the moment I entered (Yelper Eddy P is right, the front office staff do act like you're an inconvenience and so does everyone else, including the dentist I had. The only exception was Mandy, a really kind X-Ray technician I am sorry wasn't on the list in the website on the paper she gave me for a review about her service, I was going to give her a positive one in the context of the bad experience, she keeps the humanity of that place alive).

Anyway, back to the rest of the experience which makes me recommend you steer clear. While waiting, I was sent to use a bathroom that had a blood stain in it right in front of the toilet (yes, this actually happened), and when I finally got to the dentist got sighed at when I asked to add a mouth guard to my teeth cleaning and the dentist told me he would be "right back"...

At this time, it had been almost 1.25 hours of just waiting to see him, which hey, I understand, everyone gets busy.

BUT after he said he'd be back... another hour went by and still no dentist. So I asked someone I saw if they could please update me about when I would be seen.

Then, without explanation, a woman came over and, without saying anything about my dentist, told me my mouth guard and cleaning would be $490. I asked her why and she just repeated it and deducted other things to make it less expensive. She seemed surprised when I told her I had insurance. And was unapologetic about having not added or even checked for my insurance.

She then abruptly said it was an ortho surgery day and she had just gotten back from lunch, so I needed to understand. What I understood from her tone is that I was an inconvenience to her. But patiently still I told her I was frustrated with my poor treatment but thanked her for her help.

Then when it was time to pay the recalculated insurance price, she told me I couldn't get my treatments unless I had the physical FSA card I share with my husband even though they had all of his insurance info (we share the same plan) and I had pictures of the card as well as my ID and all other proof needed. This is not the upsetting part because it was only $98. What was upsetting is she told me, now 2.5 hours after arriving, that I would need to reschedule my teeth cleaning and mouth guard appointments.

I told her I wanted to speak to the manager and this is when it truly got ugly. She just said ok and took off, leaving me to wonder if I should follow so I just kind of walked behind her not knowing what to do when at least two other employees watched me and gave me stare downs. This was insult to injury because all I wanted were the simple services I'd come in for.

When told unapologetically the manager wasn't there and that maybe I could leave my number to have her call, at which point it did not seem a sincere gesture, I said I'd wait. I felt absolutely shunned at this point and like a nuisance for simply trying to be heard about what happened. Like my being frustrated was not unacceptable.

So after sitting in the waiting room quietly but feeling tension escalate and deciding I deserved better than that toxicity, I left with the manager's card (after going back up and asking, they did not offer to provide me with it).

I decided that surely this poor of treatment must stem from the top and not to push my luck. So here I am on Google Reviews trying to save others from this experience.

I'm truly sorry if you have an HMO where this is your only option. I felt physically put at risk (blood in the bathroom??) and shut down for having needs -- isn't dentistry still customer service? I have a PPO and will be going elsewhere. If you can, I advise you steer clear, too.< /review><Pictures>None< /Pictures><Response>{'time': 1555536984372, 'text': 'Megan, we are sorry to hear about your recent experience and we want to be sure that we address this issue for you. (This was my experience in 2016)

I would suggest that no one ever visit western dental for medical attention. It's been 3 days since I have visited them and my condition has done nothing, but get worse. I have two of my wisdom teeth coming in as well as a broken tooth, and after I had told the doctor that I have been taking ibuprofen and that it would not help if she prescribed it..she did. Then I go back yesterday because my throat has swollen as well as my tongue. After waiting for 3 hours, she comes into the room and tells me that she has ran out of prescription papers and that I have to go to my primary care giver to be given a stronger medication. Day 3 rolls around (Today). After only getting about 3 hours of sleep and crying almost the entire night due to the pain, I attend my family doctor. After examining me she literally said "I don't know why that dentist would do this to you." and even prescribes me Vicodin. Now I'm on my way to Western Dental YET AGAIN to see if they can do any type of procedure today considering that I have not been able to eat since the first day that I came in.<//text>

This place is warm and welcoming but above all, THIS TEAM IS EFFICENT. I have walked out of two dentist offices in Merced and drove all the way here because the offices I visited were rude and condescending.

I also have a really bad mouth due to socioeconomic reasons and youthful lifestyle choices. This has led to some really off-putting interactions with dental teams as I have been searching for someone to see long term and help me achieve a favorable dental health state.

Also I am transgender, I don't usually include this but it was openly an issue at one of the places I visited, despite me not even asking the guy to gender me properly he couldn't not be rude and politicize my mere existence. It led to me walking out despite having the worst pain of my life at the time and coming here.

When I came here I tried to hide the obvious signs of my gender expression (very poorly) and marked the male box to avoid putting the team in a situation where they might not offer me the same level of service they would someone else because unfortunately that happens and I just want my tooth pulled.

Now I mention this because the staff I first engaged with clearly noticed and used male pronouns in a very questioning but polite way. I didn't out myself because... awkwardness. But they have been able to make eye contact, treat me lile a patient and have conducted themselves in the most efficent manner I have ever seen a dental team do so thanks WD.</text>

<UserId.>117213909483342496191</UserId.><Text>If I could give them 0 Stars I would. It was horrible!!! My family and I, went to Western Dental to receive services with dental care on 10/17/2014.  He went to the office and found out he had multiple cavities and needed a root canal. He had his teeth cleaned and fluoride treatment applied. WD then looked up his credit to see if he would qualify for a dental contract. He said that he didn't want the contract until he talked to me. Stacy Bedolla put through the contract and started the payment plan without his consent or his signature. When I went to the office later that day to have my two daughter's teeth cleaned and looked at, Western Dental had cancelled our appointments without calling us without telling. Then they tried to accommodate us with almost a 1.5 hour wait time. 2.5 hours later all they had accomplished is looking at our teeth.  When I talked to Stacy Bedolla about his bill and the discrepancies, that I found out by looking at our dental insurance coverage, that Stacy had overcharged us for services which was covered under our insurance by almost $1500.00. We cancelled the subsequent appointments, because of how horrible the service was. The bays are all open with no privacy. The doctor was talking to another patient using the computer in my stall and telling all of the other patient's private information and dental issues to 8 different patients. After this we received two calls each day for collections on services that were never rendered and under a contract that was never signed. I called Western Dental on 3 occasions to get them to correct the collections, as we did not owe them anything. He called again on 10/31/2014 and talked to Cynthia. He paid $49.99 to pay for the fluoride which wasn't covered under our dental plan, which he hadn't agree to have done anyway. The calls continued twice a day with the letters that we owed them money for services they had never rendered. I contacted Leslie on 11/4/2014 to try and get the account reflected that we didn't owe them anything. The calls and the mail continued despite 3 more phone calls to request that they close the account, because it had paid in full and the other services never rendered. Magically they lost all of our information about our calls. He spoke to Jessica on 11/14/14, she stated she could not talk to him about the account, which was wrong, because it was all about him. I called on 11/17/2014 and talked to Chris which then transferred me to Victor which then transferred me to Connie (Supervisor) after a 30 minute hold time, and she said the account was closed and she would send me out a 0 balance letter.
